title: Brewing For All
author: RabidRembrandt
pages:
#- Brewing §0
§0Brewing is a craft that§0
§0has been looked at as§0
§0a useless plug-in by a§0
§0portion of the§0
§0community. It however,§0
§0is one of the fastest§0
§0way to create a§0
§0friend, or just really§0
§0fuck up your current§0
§0friends and have a§0
§0good laugh. There are§0
§0other uses
#- as well, but we can get§0
§0to that on a later§0
§0page.§0
§0
§0History§0
§0The brewing plug-in§0
§0was created October§0
§026, 2013. To my§0
§0knowledge the first Civ§0
§0iterations to start§0
§0using it was Devoted.§0
§0Keeping to a 10-20§0
§0types of drinks, all§0

#- mostly used as §0

#- roleplay friendly§0
§0drinks. One of the§0
§0sought after drinks§0
§0was the well guarded§0
§0Zyklon-B, hidden by§0
§0the Channers.§0
§0
§0Civclassics took a§0
§0swing at the plug-in as§0
§0well. GreatlordOz was§0
§0in charge of the§0
§0project of bringing§0
§0drinks to the server,§0

#- along with §0

#- the help of RektTangle§0
§0for brew creation.§0
§0Early on we had up to§0
§0around 20 drinks to§0
§0start with, until the§0
§0release of a full 150§0
§0drinks. Oz had used§0
§0the plugin to its§0
§0absolute potential to a§0
§0point I don't believe§0
§0any other server has§0
§0done.§0

#- After a few months of§0
§0the end of the Somber§0
§0War another 150§0
§0drinks were added,§0
§0doubling the amount of§0
§0drinks to be found.§0
§0Supposedly if the§0
§0server updates again,§0
§0there is another large§0
§0portion of drinks to be§0
§0added to the server.§0
§0

#- Process of Brewing§0
§0
§0Brewing can be a very§0
§0simple task, or can be§0
§0a very pain stakingly§0
§0long task. Brewing§0
§0first starts with a§0
§0cauldron with fire§0
§0underneath it, this is§0
§0used to ferment drinks§0
§0from 2 min-30 min, you§0
§0can check with R click§0
§0with
#- clock,§0

#- some drinks only take§0
§0this stage of brewing§0
§0(example being Potato§0
§0Soup, recipe in back).§0
§0
§0Next step can go§0
§0three ways from here.§0
§0Distilling, Barreling, or§0
§0Distilling then§0
§0barreling. §0
§0
§0Distilling§0
§0Distilling takes a§0

#- brewing stand that §0

#- uses a glowstone dust§0
§0as a filter inside the§0
§0top part of the§0
§0brewing stand, and§0
§0doesnt go away. You§0
§0do not need to worry§0
§0about fueling the§0
§0brewing stand with§0
§0blaze powder. After§0
§0fermentation put the 3§0
§0bottles in the brewing§0
§0stands, it will look like§0

#- it is doing nothing,§0
§0however give it time§0
§0and something will come§0
§0out. If it's indefinable§0
§0distillate it tends to be§0
§0a ruined drink, and its§0
§0back to the drawing§0
§0board, if you get§0
§0something else, you§0
§0can go to the Quality§0
§0chapter of this book§0
§0for more §0

#- information, however§0
§0leaving the drink in the§0
§0distill stand it will go to§0
§0full green quality§0
§0distill eventually and§0
§0can be pulled out at§0
§0any time.§0
§0
§0Barreling§0
§0This is the more§0
§0complex part of§0
§0brewing, since there§0
§0are 6 barrel types §0

#- dependant on wood§0
§0type. There are two§0
§0barrel sizes, the§0
§0larger one is the§0
§0storage size of a§0
§0single chest. The§0
§0smaller barrel is 1 line§0
§0of inventory space,§0
§0but you can fit more§0
§0smaller barrels in the§0
§0same space as a large§0
§0barrel. The small§0
§0barrel is 2x2 
#- wooden stair cases,§0
§0then a sign saying§0
§0"barrel" on it will§0
§0create your barrel,§0
§0these barrels can be§0
§0connected to§0
§0eachother as long as§0
§0they are still in a§0
§0barrel shape. Putting§0
§0a drink in the barrel§0
§0will start to age the§0
§0drink, and could allow§0
§0you to §0

#- discover a drink. You§0
§0are aging the drinks§0
§0so it takes a while for§0
§0this process, 1 year =§0
§020 mins irl. The longest§0
§0amount of time a drink§0
§0can take is 25 years§0
§0which is equal to 8.3§0
§0hours, but not a lot§0
§0are like this. §0
§0
§0Distilling and Barreling§0

#- This is the§0

#- longest and sometimes§0
§0trickiest brewing done.§0
§0After you follow the§0
§0distilling, you have to§0
§0figure out if the§0
§0alcohol is ageable. It's§0
§0very easy to forget§0
§0this and never truly§0
§0perfect the drink.§0
§0There have been§0
§0several times where a§0
§0drink was left §0

#- unperfected due to§0
§0never barreling the§0
§0drink. §0
§0
§0Quality§0
§0The system to fully§0
§0achieve maximum value§0
§0of your drink. There§0
§0are three tiers of§0
§0each drink, with your§0
§0objective is to attempt§0
§0to achieve the third§0
§0tier which is a colored§0

#- text version of §0

#- the drink. If you put§0
§0the drink in the§0
§0distiller or the barrel§0
§0you can check each§0
§0part of the quality in§0
§0detail, from time§0
§0fermented, distilling,§0
§0barrel age, and wood§0
§0type (if barrel aged).§0
§0It is graded from Dark§0
§0red being worst, yellow§0
§0being medium,
#- to§0

#- light green being best.§0
§0Your goal is to reach§0
§0green in all of the§0
§0requirements of the§0
§0drink, this is a§0
§0perfected drink, by§0
§0definition of§0
§0Bananagod.§0
§0
§0Tips:§0
§0-You can reverse§0
§0engineer drinks if you§0
§0leave them in barrels§0

#- long enough to see§0

#- the quality and time of§0
§0the drink. Making /brew§0
§0unlabel  Very§0
§0important.§0
§0-Write down§0
§0everything. Every§0
§0attempt you do you§0
§0should try your best§0
§0to write it down (but§0
§0hey sometimes we get§0
§0lazy and can't be§0
§0fucked). §0
§0-Spread Sheets.§0

#- -Ask to join the§0
§0brewing group chat on§0
§0the server, to either§0
§0Bananagod,§0
§0GreatlordOz,§0
§0SpiderString_.§0
§0-Use the brewing wiki§0
§0to youradvantage if§0
§0you wish to get loads§0
§0of drinks.§0
§0-Find my old spread§0
§0sheet that has 45§0
§0drinks already found§0

#- at the time.§0

#- -Mass production is§0
§0done most effectively§0
§0with 9 cauldrons in a§0
§0row, since that is a§0
§0full inventory minus§0
§0hot bar, so you can§0
§0speedly grab all the§0
§0drinks in time.§0
§0-Not all drinks are§0
§0alcoholic and are§0
§0actually helpful in§0
§0some ways and are§0
§0cheaper
#- versions§0

#- of some potions.§0
§0-There are very§0
§0creative ways to use§0
§0alcohol besides getting§0
§0drunk, think outside§0
§0the box.§0
§0-Alcohol level is§0
§0determined on a 1-100§0
§0scale, if you start§0
§0puking soul sand you§0
§0are around 80 or§0
§0above on the scale,§0
§0close to being
#- kicked§0

#- off the server.§0
§0-Milk and Baked§0
§0Potatoes are the most§0
§0viable way to get rid§0
§0of the drunkness,§0
§0keeping a cow near§0
§0your brewery is an§0
§0excellent choice.§0
§0-1 ingredient drinks§0
§0are much easier to§0
§0solve than multiple§0
§0ingredient drinks.§0
§0-Use the brew
#- clues§0

#- on the wiki to figure§0
§0out some of the drinks.§0
§0-Selling alcohol doesnt§0
§0work well with the sell§0
§0chests, so by in§0
§0person trades are the§0
§0best way around this,§0
§0or setting up a§0
§0voucher system for§0
§0drinks.§0
§0-Some drinks are§0
§0donator drinks,§0
§0meaning someone
#- made §0

#- the drink and knows§0
§0the recipe, finding§0
§0these people might§0
§0help simplify finding§0
§0out how the drink is§0
§0made.§0
§0

#- Made by Bananagod to§0
